newsitem.title: UK: NWE naphtha weighed down by prompt availabilities.
newsitem.headline: NWE naphtha weighed down by prompt availabilities.

text.p: NWE naphtha markets were quiet with levels a few dollars softer and no trade reported.
The prompt overhang continued with no petrochemical buying interest seen before around mid January, traders said.
"It's deadly quiet. Most people are on holiday and had covered their requirements before they left," one petrochemical end-user said.
He added there were good offers both for prompt and early January material but had seen little buying interest.
January swaps slipped to 219/220.50 with February around 4-5 dollars a tonne lower.
